comment.author: 39967544@N00
comment._content: This photo shows the second of Sydney's three pilot steamers, all named "Captain Cook". This vessel was built in Sydney in 1893 and took harbour pilots to and off ships until she was replaced in 1939 by a larger namesake. She was then used by the Navy as an examination vessel and to train navy cadets and army recruits. She was dismantled after the war and scuttled off the coast in 1947.
